\subsection*{6.2 Characteristics of Carbon}
- It is a member of group 14 on the periodic table, it is nonmetallic and tetravalent i.e. the four electrons are available to form covalent bonds (single, double and triple). These long covalent bonds are strong and stable. This allows carbon to form an infinite number of compounds.
